<richard iii IV.1.76>  	This was my wish: 'Be thou,' quoth I, ' accursed,
<richard iii IV.1.77>  	For making me, so young, so old a widow!
<richard iii IV.1.78>  	And, when thou wed'st, let sorrow haunt thy bed;
<richard iii IV.1.79>  	And be thy wife--if any be so mad--
<richard iii IV.1.80>  	As miserable by the life of thee
<richard iii IV.1.81>  	As thou hast made me by my dear lord's death!
<richard iii IV.1.82>  	Lo, ere I can repeat this curse again,
<richard iii IV.1.83>  	Even in so short a space, my woman's heart
<richard iii IV.1.84>  	Grossly grew captive to his honey words
<richard iii IV.1.85>  	And proved the subject of my own soul's curse,
