<richard iii IV.2.22>  	And I would have it suddenly perform'd.
<richard iii IV.2.23>  	What sayest thou? speak suddenly; be brief.
<richard iii IV.2.24>  Your grace may do your pleasure.
<richard iii IV.2.25>  Tut, tut, thou art all ice, thy kindness freezeth:
<richard iii IV.2.26>  	Say, have I thy consent that they shall die?
<richard iii IV.2.27>  Give me some breath, some little pause, my lord
<richard iii IV.2.28>  	Before I positively herein:
<richard iii IV.2.29>  	I will resolve your grace immediately.
